OL,3,CPrestigious all-girls island school
OL,4,Cresponds to cyber attack
OL,6,FOn 24 June 2024, The Ladies' College
OL,7,Fdiscovered that it was unable to
OL,8,Faccess several of its on-premises
OL,9,Fservers.
OL,11,FIt was identified that unauthorised
OL,12,Faccess had been made to some of its
OL,13,Fsystems, but the breach only impacted
OL,14,F"limited examples of personal data."
OL,16,FA spokesperson for the school stated
OL,17,Fthat while "limited data was encrypted
OL,18,Fand has since been recovered", no
OL,19,Fpersonal data, including pupil data,
OL,20,Fwas accessed during the breach.
